{"cursor":"11359","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'' (1955) features Hitchcock on a bus alongside Cary Grant.]]\n\nEnglish film director '[[Alfred Hitchcock]] made [[cameo appearance]]s' in 39 of\nhis 52 surviving major films (his second film, [[The Mountain Eagle]], is lost).\nFor the films in which he appeared, he would be seen for a brief moment boarding\na bus, crossing in front of a building, standing in an apartment across the\ncourtyard, or even appearing in a newspaper photograph (as seen in the film\n[[Lifeboat (film)|Lifeboat]], which otherwise provided no other opportunity for\nhim to appear).\n\nThis playful gesture became one of Hitchcock's signatures; and fans would make\nsport of trying to spot his cameos. As a recurring theme, he would carry a\nmusical instrument â especially memorable was the double bass case that he\nwrestles onto the train at the beginning of [[Strangers on a Train\n(film)|Strangers on a Train]]. In his earliest appearances, he filled in as\nobscure extras in crowds or walking through scenes in long camera shots. His\nlater appearances became more prominent, such as when he turns to see Jane\nWyman's disguise as she passes him in [[Stage Fright (film)|Stage Fright]], and\nin stark silhouette in his final film [[Family Plot]].\n\nHis appearances became so popular that he began to make them earlier in his\nfilms so as not to distract the audience from the plot. Hitchcock confirms this\nin extended interviews with FranÃ§ois Truffaut, Truffaut, FranÃ§ois (1968)\nHitchcock, Secker and Warburg and indeed the majority of his appearances\noccur within the first half-hour of his films.\n\nHitchcock's longest cameo appearances are in his British films [[Blackmail (1929\nfilm)|Blackmail]] and [[Young and Innocent]]. Walker, Michael (2005) [http:-\n//books.google.com/books?id=v2dnVhpwVssC&pg=PA88&dq=hitchcock+longest+cameo+bla-\nckmail&hl=en&ei=rhw_TL_7HMGJ4Qbp3vn0Cg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&v-\ned=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=hitchcock%20longest%20cameo%20blackmail&f=false\nHitchcock's motifs] Amsterdam University Press He appears in all 30\nfeatures from [[Rebecca (1940 film)|Rebecca]] (his first American film) onward;\nbefore his move to Hollywood, he only occasionally performed cameos.\n","linknr":278,"url":"List_of_Hitchcock_cameo_appearances","recorded":1375072281,"links":["/w/index.php?title=List_of_Alfred_Hitchcock_cameo_appearances&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=List_of_Alfred_Hitchcock_cameo_appearances&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/List_of_Alfred_Hitchcock_cameo_appearances","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=List_of_Hitchcock_cameo_appearances&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:HitchcockCameoToCatchAThief.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/22/HitchcockCameoToCatchAThief.png/220px-HitchcockCameoToCatchAThief.png","/wiki/File:HitchcockCameoToCatchAThief.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/wiki/To_Catch_a_Thief","/wiki/Cary_Grant","/wiki/Alfred_Hitchcock","/wiki/Cameo_appearance","/wiki/The_Mountain_Eagle","/wiki/Lost_film","/wiki/Lifeboat_(film)","/wiki/Double_bass","/wiki/Strangers_on_a_Train_(film)","/wiki/Stage_Fright_(film)","/wiki/Family_Pl